---
comment: |-
  firemon is a monitoring tool bundled with firejail. It can be abused via its pager
  to read files and spawn shells, escalating privileges if run under sudo.
functions:
  file-read:
  - code: |-
      firemon /path/to/file
    contexts:
      unprivileged:
        comment: |-
          Displays the contents of arbitrary files through its pager.
  inherit:
  - code: |-
      firemon /path/to/file
    comment: |-
      firemon inherits pager abuse patterns similar to man, less, and git.
    contexts:
      unprivileged:
    from: less
...
